cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NI 

The paper focuses on the development of a bio-inspired neural network architecture for machine learning tasks, specifically for training on very few samples. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The task of learning to read the MNIST digits involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the use of biological neural networks and their structural elements relates to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NI).
